  "text": "# Kubernetes Scheduler Plugin Framework Architecture Analysis\n\n## Overview\n\nThe Kubernetes scheduler plugin framework is implemented in the `kubernetes/kubernetes` repository with key components organized in the `pkg/scheduler/` directory. The framework uses an extensible plugin architecture that allows developers to customize scheduling behavior at multiple extension points during the pod scheduling cycle.\n\n## Framework Interface Definitions\n\nThe primary interface definitions are located in **`pkg/scheduler/framework/interface.go`**, which defines:\n\n### Core Plugin Interface\n- **`Plugin`** (line 443): The parent interface that all plugins must implement, requiring only a `Name()` method.\n\n### Extension Point Plugins\n\nThe framework defines distinct plugin types for different scheduling phases:\n\n1. **Pre-Enqueue Phase**: \n   - `PreEnqueuePlugin` (line 452): Called before pods are added to the active queue, used for lightweight filtering.\n\n2. **Queue Management**:\n   - `QueueSortPlugin` (line 464): Sorts pods in the scheduling queue (only one allowed per scheduler).\n\n3. **Pre-Filter Phase**:\n   - `PreFilterPlugin` (line 512): Called at the beginning of the scheduling cycle to compute state for filtering.\n\n4. **Filter Phase**:\n   - `FilterPlugin` (line 540): Filters out nodes that cannot run a pod (replaces old \"predicate\" concept).\n\n5. **Post-Filter Phase**:\n   - `PostFilterPlugin` (line 561): Called after filtering fails, typically implements preemption logic.\n\n6. **Pre-Score Phase**:\n   - `PreScorePlugin` (line 587): Informational plugin called after filtering, before scoring.\n\n7. **Score Phase**:\n   - `ScorePlugin` (line 607): Ranks nodes for pod placement by assigning scores.\n\n8. **Reserve Phase**:\n   - `ReservePlugin` (line 624): Updates scheduler cache state when a pod is scheduled (includes Unreserve for rollback).\n\n9. **Pre-Bind Phase**:\n   - `PreBindPlugin` (line 640): Called before binding, can perform f